17/01/2005
LONDON, Britain -- Serbia-Montenegrin President Svetozar Marovic kicked off a three-day visit to Britain on Sunday (16 January).
He is accompanied by Foreign Affairs Minister Vuk Draskovic, Defence Minister Prvoslav Davinic and Foreign Trade Relations Minister Predrag Ivanovic.
Marovic met with British Prime Minister Tony Blair and other senior government officials Monday.
He will spend Tuesday in Edinburgh, Scotland.
In other news, the new chief of Serbia-Montenegro's Army, Major General Dragan Paskas, formally assumed his duties Friday.
The ceremony took place at the Topcider military base.
(Tanjug, Beta - 16/01/05;
Danas - 15/01/05)
